The paper deals with the problem of low-rank recovery from graphs, which involves analyzing pairwise similarity between data samples and features. This problem is relevant to several areas of computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), information theory (cs.IT), and numerical analysis (cs.NA). Therefore, these are the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper.
